# Valgrind (memcheck) suppressions for the plexdb CQL server run under the
# conformance harness. Keep this list minimal — only genuine false positives.

# WAL header padding write.
#
# core/pager/pager.wal.cpp writes sizeof(wal::Header) bytes at startup. The struct
# begins with Array<U8,N> magic / Array<U8,M> version fields followed by U64 members,
# so the compiler inserts inter-field padding that designated-initialisation does not
# zero. Persisting that benign padding trips memcheck's io_submit(PWRITE) check. The
# padding is never read back as data, so this is a false positive.
#
# @note This matches any uninitialised io_submit(PWRITE); in practice only the WAL
# header write has uninitialised (padding) bytes — every other write submits a fully
# initialised buffer. Genuine data corruption surfaces as uninitialised *read* errors
# (Conditional jump / Use of uninitialised value), which are NOT suppressed here.
{
   wal-header-padding-pwrite
   Memcheck:Param
   io_submit(PWRITE)
   fun:syscall
   fun:_ZN6plexdb2osL10_io_submitEmlPP4iocb
   ...
}
